<HEADLINE>
<P>
70 LIONS IN SERENGETI KILLED BY DISTEMPER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 About 70 lions in Serengeti National Park have died from the canine distemper 
virus, and many more are infected, Tanzania's parks director said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 First detected in December, the virus has been confined so far to the central 
Serengeti and has not spread to other parts of the 5,600-square-mile park, one 
of the world's largest and most famous game preserves. 
</P>
<P>
 "It is the first time we have had such massive deaths of lions in this 
country," said Gerald Bigurube, Tanzania's director of parks. 
</P>
<P>
 There are an estimated 2,000 lions in the park. 
</P>
