<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANGELA LAKEBERG 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 What a tragedy. Angela Lakeberg died June 9 after nearly a year of struggle 
and extraordinary medical efforts. She had less than a 1% chance of survival, 
but she was subjected to a brief life of ventilators and tubes. 
</P>
<P>
 Who benefited? Certainly not Angela. She was probably in pain or discomfort 
throughout this ordeal. Imagine what must have been going on in her infant mind 
thoughout the entire time. 
</P>
<P>
 This seems to have been an ego trip for the physicians at Children's Hospital 
of Philadelphia. An extraordinary experiment without regard to the suffering or 
outcome. The physicias at Loyola Medical Center in Illinois were right when 
they refused to perform the separation on ethical grounds in view of the low 
expectation of survival. RICHARD ORFORD Hermosa Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
