<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: CARR REPLACES GAVITT IN CELTIC FRONT OFFICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Boston Celtics fired Dave Gavitt as senior executive vice president 
Tuesday and replaced him with former Celtic player M.L. Carr, who will decide 
whether former teammate Chris Ford remains as coach. 
</P>
<P>
 Gavitt will be a vice chairman of the Celtic board with unspecified 
responsibilities but will no longer be in charge of basketball operations. 
</P>
<P>
 Carr, who had been director of community relations, conceded that the decision 
was partly an outcome of a season in which the Celtics failed to reach the 
playoffs for the first time since 1979. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's been slipping over the last few months," Carr said. "Is this a reaction 
to that? Maybe to a certain degree. But I think they've picked the best guy for 
the job." 
</P>
<P>
 He said the fate of Ford remains in limbo. 
</P>
<P>
 "If Chris' plan fits what we want to do, then Chris Ford will continue to be 
the coach of the Boston Celtics," Carr said. "I reserve the right to make that 
decision until Chris and I have had a chance to sit down and talk." 
</P>
