<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISH REPORT: BRIDGEPORT LIMITS ARE LATEST LURE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Trout fishermen in search of a sure thing might want to make a trip north to 
Bridgeport where there is a lake turning out limits of good-size fish every 
day. 
</P>
<P>
 "I hate to sound like a broken record, but Bridgeport (Reservoir) continues to 
be good for limits of fish from two to five pounds," said Rick Rockel of Ken's 
Sporting Goods. 
</P>
<P>
 Rockel said most fish are taking bait in the Rainbow Bank area, and a 
7-pounder was taken from the shore Monday. 
</P>
