<HEADLINE>
<P>
HULL KEEPS HIS SHIRT ON, BLADES WIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATT WHITE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After an 8-5 victory over Oakland on Tuesday night at the Forum, Blade Coach 
Bobby Hull Jr.'s record reads: one victory, one loss, three shirts. 
</P>
<P>
 The coach of the roller hockey team had been so angry about his team's 
lethargic play in Anaheim that he had to change shirts at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
 Tuesday, Hull was happier because Tony Gruba, Steve Bogoyevac and Steve Ross 
each scored twice. 
</P>
<P>
 "The shirt made it," said Hull. "We played a lot better tonight, but I think 
we're still at about 80%. We worked on shots all week, and we improved putting 
the puck on the goal." 
</P>
<P>
 The Blades outshot Oakland, 44-29, before 4,157. 
</P>
<P>
 Blade goalie Maxim Mikhailovsky had 24 saves and gave up two goals in seven 
seconds early in the third period. The Blade defense kept the action almost 
entirely on the Oakland side of the rink for the period's last 10 minutes, 
scoring three consecutive goals. 
</P>
<P>
 Rob Mendel assisted Bogoyevac on a give-and-go fast break at 9:39 of the third 
to put the Blades ahead, 7-3.  
</P>
<P>
 "You practice plays all week, but when you get a chance at those fast breaks, 
that's what it's all about," Bogoyevac said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Blades led, 4-1, at halftime, thanks mostly to Oakland's 22 penalty 
minutes. Gruba scored twice on first-half power plays. MATT WHITE 
</P>
</TEXT>
