ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ANAHEIM; SOBRIETY CHECKS TO BEGIN WEDNESDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police will conduct a sobriety check among drivers in the city starting at 8 
p.m. today . 
</P>
<P>
 Police hold checks periodically to discourage drunk driving and heighten 
public awareness of the problem. 
</P>
<P>
 Representatives from Mothers Against Drunk Driving will be on hand at the 
police checkpoint, the location of which is not being announced in advance. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information about the sobriety checkpoint, call the Police Department 
at (714) 254-1548. 
