ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: NEWPORT BEACH; READING PROGRAM OPEN TO KIDS, TEENS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHELBY GRAD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Newport Beach Public Library's summer reading program is scheduled to 
begin June 27 and run through Aug. 20. 
</P>
<P>
 The program offers a variety of events for children and teen-agers, from an 
"independent reading club" to a toddlers' "read-to-me club." 
</P>
<P>
 Several libraries throughout the city will take part in the program, which 
will conclude in August with a festival complete with a magician and juggler. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information about registration, call (714) 644-3187. SHELBY GRAD 
