<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; MERCHANTS CAN POST WOOD RANCH SIGNS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hoping to boost flagging sales at the Wood Ranch shopping center, the Simi 
Valley City Council has agreed to allow merchants to post signs along a nearby 
roadway. 
</P>
<P>
 The council action reverses a decision by the city's Planning Commission, 
which rejected the request by Ralphs supermarket and other merchants to 
advertise their stores with a 12-foot-high lighted sign on Madera Road. 
</P>
<P>
 Shop owner Larry Lindauer told the council he was frustrated with the 
commission's decision, and that without a sign on Madera he might be forced out 
of business. 
</P>
<P>
 "The simple fact of the matter is that a sign is needed on this street," 
Lindauer said. "Please look at how your decision will affect business owners." 
</P>
<P>
 In a letter to the council, resident Denise Dean-Guerrero agreed. "The 
residents of Wood Ranch want a thriving shopping center, not a lot of empty 
storefronts." SARA CATANIA 
</P>
