<HEADLINE>
<P>
100,000 YOUTHS PLEDGE CHASTITY UNTIL MARRIAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Southern Baptist youths want a sexual revolution, and their revolt's biggest 
volley came Tuesday in a stadium-sized display of 100,000 cards pledging 
chastity. 
</P>
<P>
 Working under a broiling sun, hundreds of Baptist teen-agers placed the 
written vows in plastic holders that covered 50,000 square feet in front of the 
Orange County Convention Center, culminating a churchwide True Love Waits 
campaign. 
</P>
<P>
 Inside, the annual meeting of the Southern Baptist Convention got under way. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's a way to tell the world not to have sex before marriage," said 
13-year-old Katy Burks of Waxahachie, Tex. "It's really important to me. All my 
friends . . . are getting pregnant and it hurts to see them getting hurt like 
that." 
</P>
<P>
 Since its start more than a year ago, when 59 teen-agers took vows in a 
Nashville, Tenn., church, the True Love Waits campaign has inspired 102,000 
youths in the nation's largest Protestant denomination to pledge to abstain 
from sex before marriage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
