<HEADLINE>
<P>
KEITH SMITH LIKELY TO SIGN WITH TIGERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF FLETCHER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Keith Smith, leading passer in California high school history, is expected to 
forgo a football scholarship to Arizona to play professional baseball for the 
Detroit Tigers. 
</P>
<P>
 Smith, a fifth-round draft pick of the Tigers out of Newbury Park High, denied 
he has reached a decision but said he will make an announcement later this 
week.But Crescenta Valley infielder Kirk Hagge, who signed with the Tigers this 
week, said he expects to fly with Smith on Monday to Bristol, Va., site of the 
Tigers' rookie-league affiliate in the Appalachian League. 
</P>
<P>
 Smith's bonus package, which includes college scholarship money, is believed 
to be worth about $250,000. A shortstop, Smith batted .352 with three home runs 
and 19 stolen bases this season. JEFF FLETCHER 
