<HEADLINE>
<P>
DRIVER, 62, DIES IN SURGERY AFTER 2-CAR COLLISION IN ORANGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 62-year-old man was killed Tuesday after his car was hit by another vehicle, 
which police said may have run a red light at Cambridge Street and Katella 
Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 Burley Ray Grisham of Orange died during surgery at UCI Medical Center in 
Orange, after firefighters cut through the wreckage of his car, Lt. Trey Sirks 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Grisham was driving south on Cambridge Street just before 8 a.m. when he 
entered the Katella Avenue intersection on a green traffic signal, police said. 
His car was struck by a car driven by Paul Coe Farrier, 39, of Riverside, who 
was westbound on Katella, Sirks said. 
</P>
<P>
 Farrier was not cited, Sirks said, but traffic division officers are trying to 
determine whether his car ran a red light. 
</P>
