<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPEECH INSTRUCTOR WINS COLLEGE DISTRICT FACULTY AWARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Melinda Womack, a speech communications instructor, has received the Rancho 
Santiago College District's 1994 Distinguished Faculty Award. 
</P>
<P>
 A committee of faculty members, administrators and others chose Womack for her 
outstanding service to the district in the classroom, in the community and on 
numerous committees.She joined the district in 1987, said district spokesman 
Dale Ruhe. 
</P>
<P>
 As the winner of the annual award, Womack will be invited to present a public 
address during the 1994-95 school year, the text of which will be published in 
pamphlet form and distributed to colleges throughout the state, Ruhe said. 
</P>
<P>
 Her work on campus includes membership on the Honors Program Committee, Fine 
and Performing Arts Dean's Advisory Committee, and the Student Retention 
Coordinating Committee. 
</P>
<P>
 Womack also is active in the Faculty Assn. of California Community Colleges, 
International Communication Assn. and the Alumni Board of Directors for Chapman 
University, Ruhe said. 
</P>
