<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: VAN NUYS; MOBILE TOXIC WASTE PROGRAM TO BEGIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ED BOND 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A mobile hazardous waste collection program will roll into Van Nuys this week 
and next. 
</P>
<P>
 Dubbed the "Hazmobile" by the Los Angeles City Bureau of Sanitation, 
co-sponsor with the Los Angeles County Department of Public Works, the program 
is billed as being more convenient than the previous way of collecting 
hazardous waste in monthly roundup programs. 
</P>
<P>
 The truck and three trailers give residents an opportunity to recycle or 
safely discard such chemicals as paint, motor oil, antifreeze, furniture polish 
and insecticide. 
</P>
<P>
 The Hazmobile will be in Van Nuys from 9 a.m. to 1 p.m. Thursday through 
Saturday and from June 23-25.  
</P>
<P>
 Residents must call 1-(800)-988-6942 to make an appointment for drop-offs. 
Later, a card is mailed to them giving the exact location of collection. 
Operators accept calls on the toll-free number from 9 a.m. to 3 p.m. Monday 
through Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 The city began the Hazmobile program in February after residents complained 
that the monthly roundups forced people to wait in line for hours to dispose of 
toxic chemicals. Under the new program, residents can drive through to drop off 
their hazardous waste. If improperly stored or illegally disposed of through 
regular trash, sewers or storm drains, the waste can become health and 
environmental hazards, as well a potential cause of fire, city officials said. 
ED BOND 
</P>
</TEXT>
