<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: VAN NUYS; JOB CENTER PLANNED AT VALLEY COLLEGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ED BOND 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A center to help out-of-work residents of the northwest San Fernando Valley 
find employment will be set up Aug. 1 at Valley College under a grant from the 
city of Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 The $3.6-million grant comes from federal Job Training Partnership Act funds 
and will be spent at $1.2 million a year over three years. 
</P>
<P>
 The money will create a Comprehensive Jobs Assistance Center at the college, 
one of a network of such centers being established throughout the city. The 
centers give a wide range of employment services under one roof and are yet 
another example of "one-stop shopping" becoming popular in federal services. 
</P>
<P>
 The centers will give displaced workers job search help, referral services and 
training, as needed. Valley College is located at 5800 Fulton Ave., Van Nuys. 
ED BOND 
</P>
