Automobile Dealers Assn. seminar attributed the gains to models adapted for the 
Japanese market. Ford Motor Co. and Chrysler Corp. said their strategies are 
based on right-hand-drive cars and less expensive models they have introduced 
in Japan. General Motors Corp. said it plans to introduce right-hand-drive cars 
