<TEXT>
<P>
 Technology Marketing Inc.: The Irvine maker of electronic test products and 
mass storage systems for the computer industry said it lost $869,660, or 22 
cents a share, for its fiscal year ended Feb. 28.That compared to a loss of 
$1.5 million, or 46 cents a share, for the previous year. Revenue declined 46% 
to $1.5 million from $2.8 million. For the fourth quarter, the company recorded 
a profit of $63,850, or 2 cents a share, contrasted with a loss of $829,100, or 
26 cents a share, for the same period a year earlier. Three-month revenue 
dropped 10% to $356,531 from $397,910. 
